---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base";
import aboutImg from "../assets/Matt.jpg";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
const meta = {
  title: "About",
  description:
    "All about me Matt - Developer, Streamer, and Nerd from Sheffield",
};
export const prerender = true;
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
  <article class="about-page">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="about-header">
      <div class="header-content">
        <h1 class="page-title"><span class="accent-slash">//</span> About</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Developer / Streamer / Sheffield</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-image-container crt-filter">
        <Image
          src={aboutImg}
          height={aboutImg.height}
          width={aboutImg.width}
          alt="A Photo of Matthew Deloughry"
          loading="eager"
          class="about-image crt-image"
          transition:name={"profile-image"}
        />
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Content sections -->
    <div class="content-grid">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-accent">Hello</h2>
        <p>
          Aye up, I'm Matt<span class="strikethrough">hew</span> Peck-Deloughry,
          a web developer from Sheffield. I've been slinging code for nigh on 15
          years now and I can tell you, I've developed a reet fondness for it.
        </p>
        <p>
          You'll mostly find me professionally using PHP and Laravel, but I like
          to have a bit of fun with JavaScript, TypeScript, and Deno too.
          There's nowt I love more than creating a problem and then figuring out
          how to fix it with a bit of code. It's like a reet good puzzle!
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-info">Experience</h2>
        <p>
          I've worked on all sorts of projects in my time, big and small, and I
          always approach each one with the same level of excitement. I'm always
          looking to learn new things and improve my skills, and I love nothing
          more than bringing ideas to life through code.
        </p>
        <p>
          But it's not just about the code for me. It's about making things,
          having a bit of fun, and always looking for new challenges.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-purple">Streaming</h2>
        <p>
          Oh, and if you're up for it, you can catch me streaming my coding
          adventures on Twitch. It's a bit of a hoot, if I do say so meself!
        </p>
        <p class="disclaimer">
          Note: The above was generated by AI, asking to write a blurb for a
          Sheffield coder and nerd, born and bred!
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-pink">The Truth</h2>
        <p>
          But really I think this sums me up perfectly, I love the challenge of
          using some language I love to solve something, finding the pit-falls
          and ways out of those said holes. Finding solutions to problems is
          what it's all about - using all my "hacks" and "lessons" to produce a
          comprehensive solution.
        </p>
        <p>
          I try to share that enthusiasm in everything I do, from mentoring and
          streaming to just chatting with people. When you love what you do, it
          makes everything more fun and rewarding.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Motto quote -->
    <blockquote class="motto-block">
      <span class="quote-mark">"</span>Av' fun developing, Av' fun learning,
      then Av'a crack at engineering it!<span class="quote-mark">"</span>
    </blockquote>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about-page {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    /* Header */
    .about-header {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      gap: var(--space-xl);
      align-items: start;
      padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .header-content {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }

    /* Page title styles from global.css */

    .subtitle {
      font-size: var(--text-base);
      color: var(--theme-muted);
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* Image */
    .about-image-container {
      position: relative;
      width: 240px;
      height: 240px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .about-image {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      border-radius: var(--radius-subtle);
      filter: grayscale(100%) contrast(1.05);
      transition: filter var(--transition-slow);
    }

    .about-image-container:hover .about-image {
      filter: grayscale(0%) contrast(1);
    }

    /* Content sections */
    .content-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .content-section {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .section-heading {
      font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    .content-section p {
      font-size: var(--text-base);
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--theme-muted);
      margin: 0;
    }

    .strikethrough {
      text-decoration: line-through;
      opacity: 0.5;
    }

    .disclaimer {
      font-size: var(--text-sm) !important;
      padding: var(--space-sm);
      border-radius: var(--radius-subtle);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Motto block */
    .motto-block {
      margin: 0;
      padding: var(--space-xl);
      border: var(--border-weight) solid var(--theme-accent);
      border-radius: var(--radius-subtle);
      font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
      color: var(--theme-text);
      text-align: center;
      background: var(--theme-bg-secondary);
    }

    .quote-mark {
      color: var(--theme-accent);
      font-size: 1.5em;
      vertical-align: -0.1em;
    }

    /* Responsive */
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .about-header {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .about-image-container {
        margin: 0 auto;
        width: 180px;
        height: 180px;
      }

      .content-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</PageLayout>
